This paper discusses the resilience of scale-free networks, which are commonly used in computer science and network analysis. The paper specifically focuses on networks that approximate the degree distribution of the Internet, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also uses analytical and empirical evidence to support its findings, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), systems and control (cs.SY), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
